E SLAVONIC COLLECTION OF THE HELSINKI UNIVERSITY LIBRARY.     THE 300,000-VOLUME SLAVONIC LIBRARY OF HELSINKI UNIVERSITY LIBRARY, FINLAND,HAS RICH COLLECTIONS OF RUSSIAN-LANGUAGE AND OTHER SLAVONIC-LANGUAGEMATERIALS, PARTICULARLY FROM 1828-1917, WHEN THE LIBRARY ENJOYED LEGAL-DEPOSITRIGHTS TO ALL BOOKS PUBLISHED IN THE RUSSIAN EMPIRE. DESCRIBES THE DIFFERENTCOLLECTIONS OF THE SLAVONIC LIBRARY, ACQUISITIONS POLICIES, AND USER SERVICES